body:
Currently [Auto Find In Selection] always enable [Find In Selection] if any text is selected, which is not very practical for normal use case.

A more practical way of this is enable [Find In Selection] only if selected text contains line breaks, or even a configurable number of line breaks, i.e. auto_find_in_selection_min_lines

e.g.
with auto_find_in_selection_min_lines:2

//selected 1 lines, disable [Find In Selection]
func()

//selected 2 lines, enable [Find In Selection]
func()
func()

Then setting auto_find_in_selection_min_lines to 1 is the current behavior, setting to 2 is a more practical behavior.

It is even possible to merge with the current option: setting to 0 to disable the feature
